The paper deals with reachability analysis of hybrid systems, which are systems that exhibit both continuous and discrete behaviors. This makes cs.SY (Systems and Control) the most likely sub-category, as it specifically deals with the modeling, analysis, and control of such systems. The paper also discusses mathematical models and their approximations, which could fall under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper mentions safety analysis, which could be related to cs.MS (Mathematical Software) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as these sub-categories often deal with safety and verification of systems.
